  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (7ed07e7 2022-03-10T00:04:06.029112+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge update\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\n`forge update` does `git submodule update --init --recursive --remote`\r\n`dapp update` does `git submodule update --init --recursive`\r\n\r\nWe use `forge update` in GH actions but it breaks when we want to intentionally point to a specific submodule commit.\r\n\r\n",
